## Process

- Always orient to existing YAML in `artifacts/Home_Automation/` before writing new automations.
- Use modern HA schema: `triggers:`/`conditions:`/`actions:` as top-level keys; `trigger:` and `action:` inside list items.
- Every automation must include `mode:` -- default `single` unless queueing/restart is justified.
- Synced-switch circuits require three automations per circuit: (1) master-off cascades to children, (2) any child-on activates master, (3) all-children-off deactivates master.
- Always include `condition: state` guards on the master entity in automations 2 and 3 to avoid feedback loops.

